<Article
  title="Privacy | ZeroBeatLabs"
  description="How ZeroBeatLabs handles your data. Short version: these sites collect nothing unless you choose to send it."
>
  <h1>Privacy</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    Short version: these sites collect nothing unless you choose to send it, and
    we never sell it or add you to a mailing list. The one preview form is
    handled by a third-party processor, described below.
  </p>

  <h2>What these sites collect</h2>
  <p>
    Nothing automatically. zerobeatlabs.org, the demo at demo.zerobeatlabs.org,
    and the website previews at web.zerobeatlabs.org are static websites with no
    accounts, no cookies, and no analytics or third-party trackers. The
    interactive demo runs entirely in your browser; the data you edit there
    never leaves your device. The one exception is the optional preview-request
    form described below.
  </p>

  <h2>The website preview form</h2>
  <p>
    On web.zerobeatlabs.org you can ask for a free website preview by submitting
    your business name, email address, and an optional message. We use those
    details only to reply and to build the preview you asked for, and we do not
    add you to any mailing list. Submissions are delivered through Web3Forms
    (operated by Web3Creative), a third-party form processor acting on our
    behalf. Web3Forms stores submissions encrypted at rest and may retain them
    for up to three years before automatic deletion. To block spam, it may send
    the submitter's IP address and email address to spam-filtering providers
    (CleanTalk and Akismet), and it runs on Amazon Web Services, Cloudflare, and
    Hetzner. Full details are in the
    <a href="https://web3forms.com/privacy" rel="noopener"
      >Web3Forms privacy policy</a
    >.
  </p>

  <h2>Hosting</h2>
  <p>
    The sites are hosted on GitHub Pages. Like any web host, GitHub may log
    standard technical request information such as IP address and browser type
    for security and reliability. That data is handled under
    <a
      href="https://docs.github.com/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement"
      rel="noopener">GitHub's privacy statement</a
    >.
  </p>

  <h2>If you contact us</h2>
  <p>
    If you email
    <a href="mailto:hello@zerobeatlabs.org">hello@zerobeatlabs.org</a>, we use
    your message and email address only to respond. We do not add you to any
    mailing list, and we never sell your details.
  </p>

  <h2>No selling</h2>
  <p>
    We never sell or rent your personal information. We share it only with the
    service providers described above, and only to deliver the preview or reply
    you asked for.
  </p>

  <p class="note">Last updated 16 July 2026.</p>
</Article>
